This paper discusses the analogy between machine learning systems and economic entities, and explores how known results in economics may inform feasible solutions in AI safety, and vice versa. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also discusses decision-making and moral behaviour, which are topics related to game theory (cs.GT) and reinforcement learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper mentions the socio-economic domain, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI) and cybersecurity (cs.CY).
